f
(-\infty,-1) \cup (-1,2) \cup (2,\infty)
\lim_{x \rightarrow -1} f(x)=f(-1)
\lim_{x \rightarrow 2} f(x)=f(2).
4A+B=\lim_{x \rightarrow -1_-} -4Ax+B=\lim_{x \rightarrow -1_+} A(x^2-\tfrac{4}{x}-2)=3A
0=\lim_{x \rightarrow 2_-} A(x^2-\tfrac{4}{x}-2)=\lim_{x \rightarrow 2_+} Bx+2=2B+2.
2B+2=0
4A+B=3A.
